<br>
Why?  They govern us because we _let_ them.  If more people felt strongly about more things (and acted on them, rather than sit back and accept it), there wouldn't be nearly the levels of corruption, corporate boot licking, et all.<br>
<br>
There are people out there that are very frightened about the precident the Cali recall will set.  The very idea that if you piss off your constituates enough (be it through total inneptitude or just rotten luck &lt;wrong place, wrong time&gt;) they can AND WILL remove you, reguardless of how many more years you thought you had to rectify/cover things up or suckle at the teat that is special intrest groups breaks things.<br>
<br>
If I remember right, there are 2 other states with the recall machine just waiting to see how Cali turns out.  I'm sure those governors are sweating bulllets.<br>
<br>
The public has the potential to finally be on par, powerwise, with the mega corps.  MegaCorp has the money, but the public could very well boot you out of office.  Wheither we, collectivly are smart enough to use it responcibly is anyones guess (although all the old &quot;a group is only as smart as its dumnest member&quot; axims apply.)<br>
<br>
Of course, the most likely thing that comes from this is that  polititians spend more money/time/effort on bread and circuses to keep the masses docilly going about thier business. <p>Ninen of Saryrn<br>
